Class HashTable<K,V>

Type Parameters:

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<V>
public class HashTable<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<V>

A Hash Table class that represents associations between keys and values. An association is just a tuple . So, we might add <"foo", 12> to this hash table, associating the string "foo" with the number 12. The key "foo" is used to determine where in the hashtable the tuple is stored. Key types should have a robust implementation of hashCode().
